  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Generating Mock Data**\n\nOkay, I\'m working on the next stage. I\'m focusing on creating `/src/mockData.ts`, which will contain seed data mirroring the high-fidelity screens. I\'ve begun to extract some key figures from the Activity Page. For example, the October Savings is at +$142.50. I\'m starting to build a skeleton based on the design.\n\n\n**Expanding Mock Data**\n\nI\'m now integrating more specific data points into `/src/mockData.ts`. I\'m focused on adding entries for home charging, office commutes (thinking about how to differentiate trips), and supercharging. I\'m also including all dashboard stats, such as lifetime savings, petrol avoided, and CO2 reduction, to make the mock data richer. Plus, I\'ve added a vehicle entry with key specs like the Tesla Model 3 Long Range and a vehicle image URL.\n\n\n**Adding Vehicle Data**\n\nI\'ve incorporated additional vehicle data into `/src/mockData.ts` to enrich the simulation. I\'ve now included details for the Tata Nexon EV and MG Comet EV, complete with range, SoC, average efficiency, and total distance traveled, along with image URLs. I am considering slight adjustments to the data so they are not exact matches.\n\n\n**Calculating Session Savings**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the financial calculations within `/src/mockData.ts` to simulate session savings. I\'m working through the logic to figure out the cost savings of each charging session compared to petrol. I\'ve broken down the calculation into key steps: distance added, equivalent petrol liters, petrol cost avoided, and finally, net savings, considering electricity costs and the potential impact of solar power.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/utils.ts` which provides helper functions to calculate dynamic savings, avoided fuel (petrol) liters, and CO2 emissions saved based on the user\'s active charging sessions, live cost assumptions, and historical baseline data. This creates a realistic other-than-dry representation of actual metrics that updates in real time when new logs are added or configurations edited."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 6
      nanos: 495954264
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
