  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Finalizing LogCharging Details**\n\nI\'ve successfully finalized `LogCharging`. I\'ve implemented complete support for user-selected vehicles from the registration list. I\'m also now handling Indian standard parameters, including the Rupees (`\342\202\271`) prefix, and the estimate calculation, along with grid and road data. I think it\'s ready for deployment.\n\n\n**Reviewing Odometer Handling**\n\nI\'m now focused on the odometer readings. I\'ve ensured the capture of the odometer field and display of the current reading for the selected vehicle. I\'m verifying that the `activeVehicleId` is defaulted correctly in `/src/App.tsx`. I\'m going through the `handleAddSession` function to ensure that if the odometer reading is provided in a new session, we\'re correctly updating the vehicle\'s odometer to that exact value, rather than doing any estimation.\n\n\n**Refining Odometer Updates**\n\nI\'m revisiting the odometer update logic in `handleAddSession`. The core change is to prioritize the captured `odometerReading` from a new session, using it directly if available. Otherwise, I\'ll calculate the estimated odometer update based on energy consumed, as before. This should provide the most accurate odometer data, prioritizing user input. I\'m also ensuring the SoC gets a top-up when the session is added.\n\n\n**Improving SoC & Data Handling**\n\nI\'ve just refined the SoC update logic within `handleAddSession`. It now calculates the exact SoC percentage increase using `energyKwh` and `batteryCapacity`, ensuring precise battery state tracking. This ensures that the vehicle gets a full \'top-up\' with the new session, which is great. I am also working on `handleDeleteVehicle` and `handleClearSessions`, ensuring that the default fallback vehicle is always the Nexon EV.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now update `/src/App.tsx` to handle our corrected `LogChargingProps` format, support exact odometer logging updates from the captured session inputs, and replace any default configurations for ID `\'tesla-3\'` with `\'tata-nexon\'`."
